# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline to Transformers.js

## Context

The Transformers.js library currently has no pipeline for `image-text-to-text` tasks — where a model receives both an image and a text prompt (e.g., "Describe this image") and generates text output. The model class `AutoModelForImageTextToText` already exists in `src/models.js` (supporting LLaVA, Florence-2, Qwen2-VL, etc.), but there is no corresponding pipeline to provide a high-level API. This change adds an `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class that follows the exact patterns used by existing multimodal pipelines like `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` and `ImageToTextPipeline`.

## File to Modify

